    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-04-13T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-04-13T00:00:00-05:00" n="77"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d77">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">850d.00/344</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Department of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">British Embassy</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <p>The Department of State acknowledges the receipt of the Memorandum dated March
                    30, 1918,<note n="55" xml:id="d77fn55">Not printed.</note> from the British
                    Embassy, stating that in view of the fact that the Treaty of Peace between
                    Russia and Germany contains a clause relative to Spitzbergen,<note n="56"
                        xml:id="d77fn56">Chapter IX of the agreement, supplementary to the treaty of
                        Brest Litovsk, <ref target="frus1918Russiav01#pg_455">
                            <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1918, Russia, vol. <hi
                                rend="smallcaps">i</hi>, p. 455</ref>.</note> the British Embassy
                    has been instructed to inquire whether as it is understood that the American
                    Company there has disposed of its holding, the United States Government has any
                    interest in the question of Spitzbergen, and whether it wishes to communicate to
                    the British Government any expression of views on this subject.</p>
                <p>In reply the Department begs to state that it is not at present in a position to
                    state whether it may in the future have an interest in the settlement of the
                    affairs in relation to Spitzbergen.</p>
                <closer>
                    <dateline rendition="#left">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-04-13">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 13, 1918</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
